               <p>1402. <persName id="def1-1402-18390408" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1402-18390408" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1402-18390408" type="age" value="30"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1402-18390408" type="surname" value="CONNELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1402-18390408" type="given" value="CORNELIUS"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">CORNELIUS CONNELL</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18390408-1402-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18390408-1402-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18390408-1402-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>for stealing, on the <rs id="t18390408-cd-237" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390408-1402-offence-1 t18390408-cd-237"></join>8th of April</rs>, 4lbs. weight of lead, value 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18390408-name-1404" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1404" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1404" type="surname" value="JOHNSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1404" type="given" value="HENRY COLLIN"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390408-1402-offence-1 t18390408-name-1404"></join>Henry Collin Johnson</persName>, and fixed to a building; against the Statute, &amp;c.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390408-name-1405" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1405" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1405" type="surname" value="KINGSTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1405" type="given" value="PAUL"></interp>PAUL KINGSTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the employ of Mr. Johnson, a scavenger—the Blackwall rail-road crosses his yard—I saw the prisoner there with a pick-axe on his shoulder—he went to the leaden pipe, which if in the yard, struck it on each side, cut it off, put it under his smock-frock, and went away—I spoke to the policeman about it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390408-name-1406" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1406" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1406" type="surname" value="TAPLIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1406" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM TAPLIN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. Kingston came and told me of this—I saw the prisoner coming out of a marine-store shop, about a quarter of a mile from the prosecutor's—I went in, and inquired—I pur<lb></lb>sued, and overtook him—I said, "Where is that lead pipe?"—I put my hand on his breast, and found it in his smock-frock.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I told you I picked it up in the railway—I found it cut there, and took it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you fit the lead to the place? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, and it appeared to have been cut with some sharp instrument—it could not have been done with the pick-axe, because both the ends of that are pointed.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390408-name-1407" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1407" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1407" type="surname" value="SHAW"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1407" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM SHAW</persName>
                  </hi>. I heard the prisoner say the lead belonged to the rail<lb></lb>way—I held him while the other officer went for the prosecutor—the prisoner asked me to let him go, and keep the pipe.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390408-name-1408" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1408" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1408" type="surname" value="JOHNSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1408" type="given" value="HENRY COLLIN"></interp>HENRY COLLIN JOHNSON</persName>
                  </hi>. This lead is my property. The pipe goes</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183904080196"></xptr>
               <p>from my father's house to mine, through my yard—it was covered over and he must have dug three feet to get it—the prisoner had no business in my yard—I have seen him work in the gas-works opposite me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I went to work, and met with this bit of pipe in the railway, and I took it up.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">
                     <rs id="t18390408-1402-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-1402-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-1402-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 30.—
<rs id="t18390408-1402-punishment-232" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18390408-1402-punishment-232" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
